The Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) has cleared Sen. Ademola Adekeke, Dr. Akin Ogunbiyi and Dotun Babayemi to vie for the party’s ticket for the Osun State governorship election.  Also cleared were Alhaji Fatai Akinbade, Emmanuel Oluseye and Dele Adeleke, following the screening of the six aspirants on Wednesday. The chairman of the screening committee, Mr. Mohammed Adoke, disclosed this yesterday to reporters at the PDP secretariat in Abuja. The Osun PDP governorship primary is slated for March 9, while the election proper holds on July 16.  Source By Emmanuel Oloniruha Abuja -   The Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) governorship candidate in Osun state, Sen. Ademola Adeleke and the runner up at the primaries, Dr Akin Ogunbiyi have agreed to work together for the party’s victory in the Sept. 22 election. The News Agency reports that the two… In "Politics" By Emmanuel Oloniruha Abuja -   An Aspirant in the just-concluded Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) governorship primary election in Osun, Dr Akin Ogunbiyi, had urged the party’s leadership to declare him winner of the Saturday exercise. Ogunbiyi told newsmen on Monday in Abuja that he was at the party’s National… In "Politics" Joshua Oladipo   Osogbo   -      An Osogbo High Court in Osun has cleared Sen. Ademola Adeleke of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) to contest the Sept. 22 governorship election in the state. The Presiding Judge, Justice David Oladimeji, gave the ruling on Wednesday. Oladimeji said the plaintiff Counsel , Mr… In "Politics"